-- U.S. Municipal Debt Market Shrinks as Borrowing Falls, Fed Says
-- B y   W i l l i a m   S e l w a y
-- 2013-03-07T17:33:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-07/u-s-municipal-debt-market-shrinks-as-borrowing-falls-fed-says.html
U.S. state-and local-government debt
decreased during the last three months of 2012 as new borrowing
slipped, the  Federal Reserve  reported.  The drop pushed the size of the municipal securities market
to $3.71 trillion by the end of the year, down from $3.72
trillion at the end of September, according to figures released
by the central bank today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
